HEADWORD: Woodwork
<hw>Wood"work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Work made of wood;
that part of any structure which is wrought of wood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- Fig. the hidden parts of a building, as between the walls.⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p> Out of the woodwork. Appearing suddenly, as if from within the
walls. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Woodworm</ent>⟦br⟧
